com.analog.lyric.dimple.model.core

Class FactorGraphWalker

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.analog.lyric.dimple.model.core.FactorGraphWalker
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Iterator<INode>

    public class FactorGraphWalker
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Iterator<INode>
    An iterator that walks through connected nodes in a FactorGraph using specified searchOrder() starting from an optionally provided factor or variable node. This will only visit nodes that are reachable from the initial node and that are contained within the specified graph or one of its direct or indirect subgraphs.

      • maxRelativeNestingDepth

        See Also:

      • maxRelativeNestingDepth

        public final FactorGraphWalker maxRelativeNestingDepth(int depth)
        Sets the maximum FactorGraph nesting depth that will be explored by the search. When set to the maximum (the default) every connected node in any direct or indirect subgraph will be included. Setting it to 0 will restrict the search to nodes that are contained directly in the root graph.

        Changing this value after visiting some nodes may produce different results than setting it to that value initially.

      • maxSearchDepth

        public final int maxSearchDepth()
        Returns the maximum depth in the graph that will be searched with respect to the starting node. The default is the maximum integer value.

      • maxSearchDepth

        public final FactorGraphWalker maxSearchDepth(int depth)
        Sets the maximum depth in the graph that will be searched with respect to the starting node. Changing this value after the search has started may result in a different set of nodes visited than if that depth had been specified initially.

      • useBreadthFirst

        public final FactorGraphWalker useBreadthFirst()
        Cause nodes to be visited using BREADH_FIRST search FactorGraphWalker.Order. Changing the search order after calling hasNext() or next() will result in unpredictable behavior.
        See Also:
        useBreadthFirst(), searchOrder()

      • useDepthFirst

        public final FactorGraphWalker useDepthFirst()
        Cause nodes to be visited using DEPTH_FIRST search FactorGraphWalker.Order. Changing the search order after calling hasNext() or next() will result in unpredictable behavior.
        See Also:
        useBreadthFirst(), searchOrder()

      • searchOrder

        public final FactorGraphWalker.Order searchOrder()
        Returns the search FactorGraphWalker.Order in which nodes will be visited. The default value is BREADTH_FIRST.
        See Also:

      • next

        @Nullable
public INode next()
        Returns the next node in the graph in the given search order. Nodes that do not meet the maxSearchDepth() and maxRelativeNestingDepth() constraints will not be included. Returns null when there are no more nodes to visit. It is not necessary to call hasNext() before calling this method.
        Specified by:
